# Cloudflare Pages _redirects.
#
# History note: an earlier version had a denylist for sensitive paths
# (`/.env /404.html 404`, etc.). Cloudflare Pages does not support
# rewrites with non-200/non-3xx status codes — see
# https://developers.cloudflare.com/pages/configuration/redirects/ ("Rewrites
# (other status codes) ❌"). The presence of those unsupported rules made
# Pages skip the entire `_redirects` file, which broke the SPA catch-all
# below and caused all auth/dashboard routes (/home, /login, /signup,
# /settings, /research, etc.) to 404 in production.
#
# The dotfile/wp-admin denylist now falls through to the SPA shell, which
# renders the noindex'd NotFound view. That's harmless: those paths never
# pointed at real content, and bots probing them already know the app
# exists from the response. If we ever need a real 404 for sensitive
# paths, do it via a Pages Function or a small Worker — not via _redirects.

# ACME / well-known passthrough so cert challenges work even though the
# dotfile prefix would otherwise hit the SPA catch-all below.
/.well-known/*    /.well-known/:splat    200

# Static-asset passthroughs. Pages serves these automatically, but pinning
# them here protects against the catch-all from accidentally rewriting them
# to /index.html if Pages ever changes precedence.
/assets/*    /assets/:splat    200
/favicon.ico    /favicon.ico    200
/favicon-32.png    /favicon-32.png    200
/favicon-192.png    /favicon-192.png    200
/manifest.json    /manifest.json    200
/og-image.png    /og-image.png    200
/robots.txt    /robots.txt    200
/ads.txt    /ads.txt    200
/sitemap.xml    /sitemap.xml    200
/sw.js    /sw.js    200
/apple-touch-icon.png    /apple-touch-icon.png    200

# Legacy URL → canonical
/board    /player-rankings    301

# SPA catch-all. Anything else serves the React shell with status 200
# so client-side routing can take over. The NotFound view is noindex'd
# for genuinely unknown paths.
/*    /index.html    200
